   <abstract displayLabel="Description">The Kodak Brownie No. 2A had a case of leatherette covered card or, after 1924, metal box; metal film carrier; two reflecting finders. Case could be removed for loading by releasing two pivoted catches and pulling out the winding key. Originally priced at $3.00, the Brownie 2A introduced various appearance and technical improvements during its production run of several decades. With 116 roll film, image size was 2 1/2 by 4 1/2 inches. By 1912, over two million of these cameras were made.</abstract>
